                                <div class="row">
                                    <div class="col-md-12">
									<h2>Honors</h2>

<ul>
<li>Life-time <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Docent" target="_blank">Docent</a> title awarded by the Rector of University of Turku, Finland, 2016.</li> 
<li><a href="https://ec.europa.eu/research/participants/portal/desktop/en/opportunities/h2020/calls/h2020-msca-if-2016.html#c,topics=callIdentifier/t/H2020-MSCA-IF-2016/1/1/1/default-group&callStatus/t/Forthcoming/1/1/0/default-group&callStatus/t/Open/1/1/0/default-group&callStatus/t/Closed/1/1/0/default-group&+identifier/desc" target="_blank">Global Marie Curie Fellowship</a> awarded by the <strong>European Union (EU)</strong> with the score of 94.5% (success rate EU-wide < 10%), 2016.</li>
<li>Nominee for <strong>"The Teacher of the Year"</strong> at University of Turku, chosen by students (university-wide), 2016.</li>
<li><strong>Rank 10</strong> by number of publications at University of Turku (among <strong>544</strong> authors <strong>in the field of engineering</strong>) over the period 2011 to 2015, according to <strong>Elsevier SciVal</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Rank 10</strong> by number of publications at University of Turku (among <strong>544</strong> authors <strong>in the field of computer science</strong>) over the period 2011 to 2015, according to <strong>Elsevier SciVal</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Rank 52</strong> by number of publications at University of Turku (among <strong>4893</strong> authors <strong>in all subject areas</strong>) over the period 2011 to 2015, according to <strong>Elsevier SciVal</strong>.</li>

<li><strong>Best Paper Award</strong> from International Conference on IoT Technologies for Health Care, 2015.</li>

<li><strong>Best Paper</strong> Candidate in 25th IEEE DFT Symposium.</li>
<!--<li>Meritorious Service Certificate From IEEE Computer Society as <strong>"Top Reviewer"</strong> for <strong>IEEE Transactions on Computers</strong>, 2014.</li> -->

<li><strong>Ulla Tuominen</strong> Foundation Research Excellence Award, 2012.</li>

<li><strong>Best Student Paper Award</strong> from IEEE International Symposium on Defect and Fault Tolerance in VLSI and Nanotechnology Systems (DFT) Sponsored by <strong>Intel Corporation</strong>, 2011.</li>
<li><strong>Nokia</strong> Foundation Research Excellence Award, 2011.</li>


<li><strong>Nokia</strong> Foundation Research Excellence Award, 2010.</li>


<li>Iran Telecommunication Research Center <strong>(ITRC)</strong> Research Excellence Award, 2007.</li>
</ul>

